implementation_notes:
Architecture: Single values.schema.json file placed at operators/keystone/helm/keystone-operator/values.schema.json alongside Chart.yaml and values.yaml. Helm auto-discovers this file. No code changes to templates needed.

Schema structure mirrors values.yaml hierarchy:
- Root object with additionalProperties: false
- image: { repository (string), tag (string), pullPolicy (enum) }
- replicas: integer, minimum 1
- resources: { limits: { cpu, memory }, requests: { cpu, memory } } with K8s quantity patterns
- rbac: { namespaceScoped (boolean) }
- leaderElection: { enabled (boolean) }
- webhook: { enabled (boolean) }
- metrics: { port (integer, 1-65535) }
- serviceAccount: { create (boolean), name (string) }
- nameOverride: string (optional, from _helpers.tpl)
- fullnameOverride: string (optional, from _helpers.tpl)

Potential pitfall: helm-unittest sets values via 'set:' blocks which internally go through schema validation. Ensure the schema allows all value combinations used in existing tests. Verify by running helm unittest after adding schema.

K8s resource quantity pattern: Use a permissive regex that covers the common formats (integer, decimal, millicpu suffix, binary/SI memory suffixes) without being overly strict.
